OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,373,370,120,260,000,100
PN,37207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F372A1782391699
OL,3,CMayor unveils first ever 'heat plan'
OL,4,Cto help Londoners during heatwaves
OL,6,FFurther analysis was said to have
OL,7,Ffound that around one million homes in
OL,8,FLondon may currently be at high risk
OL,9,Fof overheating, with more than 1,300
OL,10,Fschools, 60 hospitals and 351 care
OL,11,Fhomes located in high heat risk areas.
OL,13,FLondon fire commissioner Jonathan
OL,14,FSmith said: "Extreme heat is no longer
OL,15,Fan occasional challenge, it's becoming
OL,16,Fan increasingly regular risk for
OL,17,FLondon, as demonstrated just this week.
OL,26,@vD@MOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G7/10
